# Flair

The Flair component, used on marketing front doors, helps users quickly scan content for important information and to view categorized content. It is used to display contextual or decorative information (e.g. Blog, Article, Video, Sale, Discount, etc) that is not a state.

This component is not a replacement for Text Badges. Use Text Badge to display contextual information related to state (information, warning, error, positive, new, etc)

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/flair
```

```tsx
import { Flair } from '@ids-ts/flair';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `size` | `'small' | 'medium'` | No | The size of the flair |
| `colorStyle` | `keyof typeof colorStyles` | No | Color 2.0 theme of flair component |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface FlairProps extends React.ComponentProps<'div'> {
  /** The size of the flair */
  size?: 'small' | 'medium';
  /** Color 2.0 theme of flair component */
  colorStyle?: keyof typeof colorStyles;
}
```

</details>

## Design Variants

The following variant axes control the component's visual appearance:

### Color → use prop `colorStyle`

- `2.0` **(default)**
- `1.0`

> **2 design variants** are defined in Figma. [View in Figma](https://www.figma.com/design/VO8rsMYDqsDY44J9yEVyES9Y?node-id=42287%3A193066&m=dev)

